LIMPOPO cops have launched manhunt for thugs who robbed a cash van in Letsitele outside Tzaneen. National Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Brenda Muridili said it is alleged that a bakkie was used to ram the armoured van off the road. Muridili said it happened on the R71 between Litsitele and Tzaneen on Monday afternoon. She said an unknown number of suspects then pointed the two security guards with firearms, disarmed them. Muridili said they used explosives to blow up the cash van, then fled the scene in three vehicles with an undisclosed amount of cash. She said the police have opened cases of cash in transit robbery.